ttp_template:
<group name="type_network_interface">
{{TYPE}} {{NETWORK}} is directly connected, {{INTERFACE | ORPHRASE}}
</group>
<group name="type_network_cost_next_hop_time_interface">
{{TYPE}} {{NETWORK}} [{{COST}}] via {{NEXT_HOP}}, {{TIME}}, {{INTERFACE | ORPHRASE}}
</group>
cli_content:
IPv6 Routing Table - Default - 15 entries
Codes: C - connected, S - static
       U - per-user static route, B - BGP
       R - RIP, D - EIGRP, EX - EIGRP external
       ND - ND Default, NDp - ND Prefix, DCE - Destination Controlled Extension
       NDr - Redirect, O - OSPF Intra, OI - OSPF Inter
       OE1 - OSPF External Type 1, OE2 - OSPF External Type 2, ON1 - OSPF NSSA Type 1
       ON2 - OSPF NSSA Type 2

C   2001:DB8:1::/48 is directly connected, Ethernet0
D   2001:DB8:2::/48 [90/30720] via FE80::1, 00:02:00, Ethernet1
B   2001:DB8:3::/48 [200/0] via 2001:DB8:FF:1::1, Ethernet2
S   2001:DB8:4::/64 [1/0] via 2001:DB8:FF:2::2

C   FF00::/8 is directly connected, Null0
textfsm_template:
Value TYPE (\S+)
Value NETWORK (\S+)
Value COST (\d+[\/\d+]*)
Value NEXT_HOP (\S+)
Value TIME (\S+)
Value INTERFACE (\S+)

Start
  # Match connected routes
  ^\s*${TYPE}\s+${NETWORK}\s+is\s+directly\s+connected,\s+${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
  # Match other routes
  ^\s*${TYPE}\s+${NETWORK}\s+\[${COST}\]\s+via\s+${NEXT_HOP},\s+${TIME},\s+${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
